{:metadata {:description [{"text" "<p>Arp2/3 binds to pre-existing actin filaments and nucleates new daughter filaments, and thus becomes incorporated into the dynamic actin network at the leading edge of motile cells and other actin-based protrusive structures [[cite:PUB00035127]]. In order to nucleate filaments, Arp2/3 must bind to a member of the N-WASp/SCAR family protein [[cite:PUB00020552]]. Arp2 and Arp3 are thought to be brought together after activation, forming an actin-like nucleus for actin monomers to bind and create a new actin filament. In the absence of an activating protein, Arp2/3 shows very little nucleation activity. Recent research has focused on the binding and hydrolysis of ATP by Arp2 and Arp3 [[cite:PUB00035128]], and crystal structures of the Arp2/3 complex have been solved [[cite:PUB00022758]].</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The human complex consists of Arp2/3 complex composed of ARP2, ARP3, ARPC1B/p41-ARC, ARPC2/p34-ARC, ARPC3/p21-ARC, ARPC4/p20-ARC and ARPC5/p16-ARC.  This family represents the ARPC4/p20-ARC subunit.</p>", "llm" false, "checked" false, "updated" false}], :is-reviewed-llm false, :representative-structure {"accession" "1k8k", "name" "Crystal Structure of Arp2/3 Complex"}, :overlaps-with [{"accession" "IPR034666", "name" "Arp2/3 complex subunit 2/4", "type" "homologous_superfamily"}], :member-databases {"panther" {"PTHR22629" "ARP2/3 COMPLEX 20 KD SUBUNIT"}, "pirsf" {"PIRSF039100" "Actin-related protein 2/3 complex subunit 4"}, "pfam" {"PF05856" "ARP2/3 complex 20 kDa subunit (ARPC4)"}}, :is-updated-llm false, :name {"name" "Actin-related protein 2/3 complex subunit 4", "short" "ARPC4"}, :wikipedia nil, :source-database "interpro", :type "family", :counters {"structures" 35, "domain_architectures" 72, "proteomes" 2458, "taxa" 10320, "subfamilies" 0, "interactions" 0, "matches" 5377, "sets" 0, "proteins" 5271, "structural_models" {"alphafold" 2936}, "pathways" 24}, :integrated nil, :cross-references {}, :set-info nil, :accession "IPR008384"